        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Regali satis congruit excellencie ut
                        peticionibus servorum Dei libenter aures accomodet et eorum effectus devote
                        tractando utiliter instituit, quatinus id agendo et eos in divinis cultibus
                        fervenciores reddat, et pro his apud Dominum devotis eorum precibus eternam
                        remunerationem percipiat. Omnium igitur sancte Dei Ecclesie nostrorumque
                        presencium scilicet ac futurorum comperiat industria, eo quod <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/232">Petrus</persName> venerabilis <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/108">sancte <placeName ref="#places/191"
                                >Regensis</placeName> ecclesie</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">presul</rs> per <persName ref="#people/155"
                            key="#Intercessory #Queen #marriage">Bertilam</persName>
                        <rs key="#marriage">dilectam coniugem</rs> et <rs key="#Queen">consortem
                            regni</rs> nostri nostre suggessit <rs key="#Intercessory"
                            >mansuetudini</rs>, ut quasdam res eclesie sue, quas quondam beate
                        memorie <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/164">Sigefredus</persName>
                        eiusdem ecclesie <rs key="#Bishops">pontifex</rs> in <rs key="#Canons"
                            >kanonicorum</rs> ibidem <orgName
                            key="#Curtes #Mansi #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Wine #Immunity #Exemption #Collegiate_churches #Canons #Royal_slave"
                            >Deo beateque Dei genitricis semperque virginis Marie sanctique
                            Michahelis Archangelo Dei</orgName> militancium usibus cotidianisque
                        vite stipendiis ad utiliorem transferens ordinem divina inspiracione
                        constituit, et postmodum tam ab eiusdem ecclesie pontificibus quamque et <rs
                            key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines">bonis hominibus</rs> Deum timentibus eidem
                            <rs key="#Collegiate_churches">kanonice</rs> oblate sunt, nos pro Dei
                        omnipotentis amore animeque nostre omniumque parentorum nostrorum mercede
                        nostra regali plenius ac firmius auctoritate corroboraremus, quatinus eisdem
                        Dei famulis largicionis nostre fultis presidiis devocius Dei famulatum
                        exequi et pro nobis attencius. Domini misericordiam exorare delectet. Nos
                        autem tanti pontificis precibus assencientes, hoc nostre confirmacionis
                        apices fieri iussimus, per quos omnino decernimus atque statuimus, ut ab
                        hinc in futurum omnes res, que prefate kanonice oblate sunt vel oblate
                        fuerint, perhenniter stabilite permaneant. <rs key="#Churches">Ecclesia</rs>
                        scilicet <orgName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/102">Sancti Michahelis Archangeli</orgName> et
                            <orgName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >Sancti Peregrini</orgName>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/103">Sanctique Faustini</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >Sancti Vitalis</orgName> cum omnibus pertinenciis earum et in
                            <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/196">Gavasa</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">massaricia duo</rs>, et de parte
                            <persName key="#Count"><name ref="Erembertus"
                            >Heremberti</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">massaricium unum</rs>, et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra cum <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs></rs>
                        prope <rs key="#Mountains">montem Gammoni</rs> qui Corte Duci vocitatur, et
                            <rs key="#Curtes">corticellas quattuor</rs> in montanis, et hec sunt
                        nomina earum: <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/134"><placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/236">Villa</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1420"><placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Toano</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1421"><placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Massa</placeName></geogName> et <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/133"><placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/240">Piriniano</placeName></geogName>, seu et <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">massaricium</rs> unum in <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Royal_slave"
                            ref="#places/235">Maxenciatico</placeName> cum <rs key="#Royal_slave"
                            >famulis et famulabus</rs>, verum etiam <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >sortes duas</rs> in <placeName ref="#places/1833"
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Argene</placeName> prope <geogName ref="#estates/1423" key="#Curtes"
                            >corte qui <placeName key="#Curtes">Nova</placeName> dicitur</geogName>,
                        seu et <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/110">Sancti Laurencii</orgName> quam <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/178">Azzo</persName> venerabilis episcopus
                        predictis kanonicis concessit cum omnibus pertinenciis suis, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">campum</rs> etiam unum inter <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Mandrie</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Mandriole</placeName> coniacentem qui Centumiuges nominatur, insuper
                        etiam et omnibus <rs key="#Mansi">mansis</rs> et rebus seu familiis
                        utriusque sexus quas bonos et Deo timentes ipsis kanonicis ad cotidianum
                        victum habere disposuerunt homines. Hec omnia sepe nominati kanonici cum
                        plenissima largitate possideant, et cuncta quecumque preteritis aut futuris
                        temporibus in eadem kanonica a benignis largitoribus aucta fuerint, per hanc
                        nostra institucionem et confirmationem ac inviolabilem corroboracionem
                        stabilita et fixa permaneat, ut <rs key="#Immunity #Exemption">nullus
                            ecclesie presul eiusdem sedis vel aliqua rei publice nostre potestatis
                            ullo umquam in tempore de prefata kanonica rebusque et familiis seu
                            precariis vel libellariis aliquam violenciam vel diminoracionem facere
                            presumat</rs>. Si quis contra hanc nostram confirmacionem insurgere
                        temptaverit, aut aliquam violenciam pretaxatis kanonicis facere quesierit,
                        noverit se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">quingentas libras auri
                            obrizi</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem palacio nostro</rs> et
                            <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem ipsi
                            kanonice</rs> et in eadem militantibus. Et ut hec nostre confirmacionis
                        auctoritas ab omnibus verius credatur diligenciusque observetur, manu
                        propria subter eam confirmavimus et anuli nostri impressione insigniri
                        iussimus. Signum domni (M) Berengarii serenissimi regis. <persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> iussu regio recognovi et subscripsi.
                        (SR) (SI n. II) Dat. VIII id. novembris, anno domni Berengarii serenissimi
                        regis XX, indictione XI. Actum <placeName ref="#places/65">Papie</placeName>
                        palatio regio. In Dei nomine feliciter, amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
